<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17261] Core loading is capped at 60 seconds</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17261</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A combination of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16187&quot; title=&quot;ExecutorUtil#awaitTermination shouldn&amp;#39;t wait forever&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-16187&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-16187&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (giving a 60 second time limit to shutting down &lt;tt&gt;ServiceExecutor&lt;/tt&gt; pools) and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16577&quot; title=&quot;Core load issues are not always logged&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-16577&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-16577&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (simplifying the core load logic), meant that core loading is interrupted and stopped after 60 seconds.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can either:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Revert the core load simplifying logic (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16577&quot; title=&quot;Core load issues are not always logged&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-16577&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-16577&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)z&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add another &lt;tt&gt;awaitTermination()&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;ExecutorUtil&lt;/tt&gt; that does wait forever (or until an interrupt), that should be used when not in a &lt;tt&gt;close()&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;shutdown()&lt;/tt&gt; method&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I think Option 2 is the cleaner approach and will help others using the same method of shutting down and waiting on an &lt;tt&gt;ExecutorService&lt;/tt&gt; to block on the completion of a set of async tasks.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
